<plot>The protagonist in this picture is legendary Bulgarian Khan Krum - a ruler in 7th c. In this period, Bulgaria ranked third in Europe in terms of territory and military power. It is Khan Krum who contributed to the union of Bulgarians and Slavs. He enforces unseen to that day laws against calumniators, thieves, violators. It stirs discontent among his closest men. The ruler is smart and just, but isn't he too severe? At what cost can one ensure order and progress in a state?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?137019</url></doc>
